5:
Perhaps we should call it a day. It's
probably getting dark outside, so we
should set up camp.
9:
Sounds good to me. At the rate
we're going, we'll finish the job by
tomorrowâ€”
12:
I can keep going, Ernest! I'll get lots
done while you all rest up...
15:
It's okay. The orphanage said to not
work too hard, right?
17:
But I really appreciate it. Thanks for
always working so hard.
21:
...Johan sure does put in a lot of
effort. He's been really helpful.
25:
I'm a little worried, though. It's
dangerous for children to do work
like this.
30:
...I made sure to remind him not to
wander too far.
33:
Even still, I want to let Johan do what
he wants. I understand how he feels...
36:
...Hey, Stella. Do you think I'm being
helpful to Ernest?
42:
Oh, good! He's always so nice to me,
so I want to return the favor however
I can...
45:
I wouldn't want to be hated by
somebody again...
53:
Everything's okay, Johan. Nothing to
be afraid of now.
56:
I-I'm so sorry... I promise I'll never get
in your way again.
62:
I'm just happy you're safe, Ernest.
That's all I care about.
65:
Let's set up camp. There may still be
monsters in here, so let's head out
for now.
74:
...I think he's afraid of the same thing
happening to him again.
76:
He forces himself to be useful and to
be loved by everyone... Always
careful to stay in everyone's good
graces.
81: Is there anything we can do to help?
85:
Being there for him is the best we
can do.
88:
But even then, it may be difficult for
Johan to fully recover from what
he's lost.
91:
...I've gone through the same
experience as him, you see.
94:
There are many reasons why a child
may be left without parents. Just like
Johan, my parents abandoned me.
99:
Is this why you wish to help him as
much as you do?
103:
...Johan and I are much the same.
He's always so kind to everyone,
hoping to one day find a place of his
own to call home.
106:
Trying to be so kind all the time is
exhausting, and sometimes you
even hate yourself for it.
109:
...I don't think a day will come where
the pain is ever truly gone.
112:
No matter how bright the days
ahead are, I don't think we'll ever be
able to ignore what was lost in the
past.
116:
...And yet you still strive to smile
before everyone.
120:
That's because the people around
me have shown me true kindness.
123:
The folks at the orphanage, the
people in the city, and Father, too... I
couldn't be more thankful for them.
126:
I want Johan to know that kindness,
too.
128:
Even if you can't get over the past,
and even if you can't love yourself...
You can still find happiness.
131:
...Perhaps I'm speaking little more
than dramatic nonsense.
136: You weren't, Ernest. Not at all.
138:
...It's about time we got some sleep,
too.
151:
I am. That's why I try so hard to be
loved by everyone.
166:
This is a very rare find, Johan! Great
work!
172:
Hey, Johan. Watch what happens
when this mineral is exposed to
magic.
175:
Quite a sight, isn't it? Magic causes it
to glow like this.
178:
The color depends on the magic.
The light you're seeing now came
from you.
181:
...Th-this... This is crazy! I never knew
rocks like this existed!
184:
This world has plenty of sights I'm
sure you'd be delighted to see. Let's
try going to a new place next time.
187:
We'll have to stay diligent and
prioritize safety, but I'd be happy to
train you.
190:
O-okay! You're an awesome
teacher, Ernest!
196:
As long as I can keep putting a smile
on everyone's face, I must be doing
something right.
